column13: Backwater conditions due to ice cover.
column14: Measured in narrows below gauge.  Could not obtain panels at LHB or RHB due to thin ice conditions.  Likely to bring down measurement accuracy but likely a decent trade off to get bins nearly to the bottom of river as measureing upstream where banks have good ice the river is too deep and the ADCP does not profile to bottom.  Altered good ensemble per cells from 1 to 4 in SxS to remove bin showing -0.4m/s on panel 13.  This velocity is unlikely given the velocities recorded at other portions of the river.  Some negative velocities near bottom recorded in other panels but not to that magnitude. Q changed from 5.26 to 5.42.  Took water level in line with gauge about mid river.  Could not locate primary BM as it was buried under snow and is not labelled with a marker of any kind.  Used NT98-2 instead. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column13: Open approx 20m ds measurement section. Hinged ice that has receded and broken. Thin ice or frozen pooled overflow approx 50m us gauge near right bank. Two layers of ice on near left bank at measuerement section - noticed on abnormally thick ice panel (approx 0.5) between two panels of ice thickness approx 0.3m.
column14: Measurement approx 50m ds gauge, as far downstream as safe. Attempted StreamPro measurement (M1), not profiling to bottom, only top 20-30%, aborted that measurement. Switched to M9 (M2 - imported) which did slightly, but not significantly better. Fair measurement overall. Assume clear water/low SNR related, although SNRs seem high enough for at least the first 3m from the SNR diagram. Unsure if this is a longstanding problem. Looking at previous measurement, RiverPro performed better and is probably the instrument of choice for this station. Was looking out for beam 2 separation which had been observed with this instrument by another tech at a different station - no noticable beam 2 separation although all 4 beams seem to separate to a greater extent than normal at around 3m despite total depth of almost 5m. Unsure of the cause or impact on measurement, but the measured discharge is in line with what was expected. Some difficulty levelling tripod/total station in soft/settling/melting snow. Does not seem to have affected levels. Mid-section
GC: 0.000 HG: 6.249 SRC: -0.003 No Reset (NR)

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Clear , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: B conditions due to ice cover.
column14: Measured ds of gauge at constriction.  Nearly in the narrow part of the channel.  Had to remeasure the first 5.5m of mmnt.  SxS was calculating flows in negative.  Checked bank as LHB in software and was correct.  After panel 5.5 stopped pinging to open measurement wizard and checked that the software was set to Y velocity, correct also.  Started pinging again and velocities in new measured panels positive, went back and remeasured previous panels.  Cause is unknown but it is believed the software/RPRO was measuring in magnitude velocities even though it was not set to that option.  MGH calculated on Field Review tab. Setup total station on ice.  Used BM marked by ground rod.  Drilled hole nearly in middle of channel, slight overflow of water out of auger hole (approx 20mm).  Did not appear to affect DWL as SRC is minimal. Mid-section
